In the Meadow

In the meadow green and wide  
Where the flowers bloom and play,  
Let the heart therein abide,  
Savoring the golden day.

Listening to the songbirds' cheer  
Echoing above their throne,  
In the joy, let us not fear,  
For the meadow is our own.

---

- Oliver Wendell Holmes Sr
